<h1 class="hero-h">Otter vs Fathom: <em>head-to-head comparison.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Otter and Fathom both produce AI meeting summaries, both integrate with major video platforms, both have free tiers. They're aimed at different users. Picking based on use case rather than features lands you in the right place.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">The take</div><p class="verdict-p">Two years ago Otter Pro was the default. In 2026 it isn't. Fathom's free tier ships unlimited recordings, unlimited transcripts, and a summary email that's cleaner than what Otter charges $17/mo for. For any individual operator or team under 10 people, there's no case for Otter over Fathom on features or price. Where <strong>Otter</strong> still wins is admin at scale: SSO, audit logs, org-wide meeting analytics, retention controls. If you're a 200-person company where compliance owns the tool, Otter still makes sense. If you're anyone else, <strong>Fathom</strong>.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
